				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Blizzard can do what they want and when they want with WOW. 
<br />

<br />
IGE is making money off of Blizzard's work. ALOT of money. (Don't even try to say 'But they are selling the TIME players invested! not the actual item!!) Blizzard is right for taking this stance, personally i'd have done it in a much meaner manner - create swat teams , 5 guys per server with a bunch of fake paypal accounts, "purchase" the items from the site, and ban that credit card/IP address/account. bada-bing-badaboom. IGE/etc is out 50$ + whatever items were on that account. If you did that to oh 100 accounts. You'd effectively shut them down as they couldn't make trades without doing 10 thousand steps around stuff - like verification etc (oh wait! thats time spent - which is money lost.) 
<br />

