			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While I applaud Blizzard's attempt to prevent destruction of the game economy by going after those that sell gold, items, and accounts - in the end they will be as successful as the war on drugs and the RIAA's attempts to stop music downloading.
<br />

<br />
Some thoughts:
<br />

<br />
They could be successful in putting * / * / etc. out of business (in name - doesn't mean they couldn't open up another business doing the same thing).
<br />

<br />
Banning IP Addresses is ludicrous.  Chances are if you have broadband, everytime your cable or dsl modem reboots you're on a different IP.  This is certainly true with 99% of commercial dialup accounts.
<br />

<br />
The IP (intellectual property) approach to the C&D letter (and potentially to a lawsuit) is actually quite good.  Courts have given wide berth to IP suits in the past 10-15 years.  Laws like the DMCA and jurisprudence give them significant weight.
<br />

<br />
-edit-
<br />

<br />
At the end of the day - if your business is making money on the back of someone else's intellectual property, and they don't like - you will lose in court every time.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
